Where the reporting party has a corporate trustee, indicate whom the director of the corporate trustee is representing.

An individual may represent one and only one of the following: Employer - where the individual is an employer representative. Member - where the individual is a member representative. Independent - where the individual is an independent trustee (i.e. a trustee who does not represent members or employers, but not a director of a professional trustee company.) Professional - for directors of a professional trustee company.
